The paper discusses the security of machine learning algorithms and systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the different phases of machine learning, such as training and operation, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning in tasks such as security surveillance and autonomous vehicles, which could fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively. Finally, the paper mentions the impact of malicious input samples on the learning process, which could also relate to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
